<h3 id="actions-by-twitter-and-facebook">Actions by Twitter and Facebook</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Both have worked on combating foreign interference campaigns for elections around the world since 2016</li>
  <li>Facebook created the War Room, an extra team focused on interference<sup>15</sup></li>
  <li>Facebook has greater transparency for the origin of groups and clearly label posts from state-owned media</li>
  <li>Both have shut down accounts with ‚Äúcoordinated inauthentic behavior,‚Äù such as spam<sup>8</sup></li>
  <li>Both have met directly with presidential campaigns<sup>15</sup></li>
</ul>

